---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | WorkMultiple"
  description="WorkMultiple's privacy policy. How we collect, use, and protect your information."
>
  <Header />

  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container content-inner">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-meta">Effective March 4, 2026</p>

      <p>WorkMultiple ("we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy. This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and how we protect it. We keep this straightforward because that is how we operate.</p>

      <h2>What We Collect</h2>
      <p>When you subscribe to our newsletter or purchase a product, we may collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your email address</li>
        <li>Your name (if provided)</li>
        <li>Payment information (processed securely by our payment provider, not stored by us)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We may also collect your name and email address if you contact us directly via email.</p>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information you provide to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Send you our newsletter and practical AI guides</li>
        <li>Deliver digital products you purchase (such as playbooks)</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about your account or purchases</li>
        <li>Improve our content and services</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

      <h2>Tools and Services We Use</h2>
      <p>To run our business and communicate with you, we use the following third-party services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Beehiiv</strong> for email newsletters and subscriber management. Beehiiv's privacy policy applies to data processed through their service.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Workspace</strong> (including Gmail) for email communication. Google's privacy policy applies to data processed through their services.</li>
        <li><strong>Netlify</strong> for hosting this website. Netlify may collect standard server logs (such as IP addresses and browser type) as part of normal website hosting.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> for understanding how visitors use our website. This collects anonymized usage data such as pages visited, time on site, and general location. No personally identifiable information is collected through Analytics.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>Our website uses cookies from Google Analytics to understand site traffic and usage patterns. These are standard analytics cookies and do not track you across other websites. You can disable cookies in your browser settings at any time.</p>

      <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <p>Your information is stored within our third-party service providers (Beehiiv, Google Workspace), which provide industry-standard security including encryption in transit and at rest. We do not store your personal data in any other systems beyond what is necessary to communicate with you and deliver our products.</p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You can request to see, update, or delete any personal information we hold about you at any time. You can also unsubscribe from our newsletter at any time using the link in any email we send. Just email us and we will take care of it promptly.</p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>If we make meaningful changes to this policy, we will update the effective date at the top of the page. We encourage you to review this page periodically.</p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy or how we handle your data, reach out to us at <a href="mailto:emilio@workmultiple.com">emilio@workmultiple.com</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-content {
    padding: 4rem 0 6rem;
  }

  .content-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-meta {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #888888;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.7em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-border);
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(233, 89, 74, 0.3);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
